@database Geometry
@node "main" "Geometry V1.6"

 @{b}Geometry V1.6 (c) Francesco Agnoli 1997-98@{ub}

 Program for geometrical calculations, written 100% in assembler. It
 calculates a lot of parameters of squares, rectangles, parallelograms,
 triangles, trapeziums, regular polygons, circles, ellipses, prisms,
 cylinders, tetraeders, pyramids, cones, octaeders, dodecaeders,
 ikosaeders and vectors. You must enter only some values until the
 program can start the calculation of all remaining parameters. These are
 shown in a window and may be saved in a file. A 2D-plot of the
 calculated figures can be displayed and saved as a IFF-ILBM file.
 Geometry uses IEEE double precision math libraries, 'reqtools.library'
 and 'iff.library'. It requires Amiga OS 2.04 or higher and can be used
 with any 680x0 processor.

      @{"REQUIREMENTS - INSTALLATION           " link "Requirements"}

      @{"WORKBENCH TOOLTYPES - SHELL PARAMETERS" link "Tooltypes"}

      @{"REGISTRATION                          " link "Registration"}

      @{"HISTORY                               " link "History"}

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Installation - Requirements"

 Use the included installer-script to install the program on your
 (hard)disk.

 To run this program you need following files:

 - Geometry                                         (main program)
 - Geometry.catalog                               in the directory
                                        LOCALE:catalogs/deutsch or
                                     LOCALE:catalogs/italiano etc.
                 (if you want to use other languages than English)
 - You need the libraries "mathieeedoubbas.library",
   "mathieeedoubtrans.library" and "reqtools.library" (v38)
   in your "LIBS:" directory
 - Geometry does not need iff.library to run, but it cannot save
   its graphical output without this library.

 Geometry requires OS 2.04+, but was only tested under OS 3.1.
 It opens its windows on the workbench screen or another pubscreen,
 that must have a minimum size of 640x400.

@endnode

@node "Tooltypes" "WORKBENCH TOOLTYPES - SHELL PARAMETERS"

 You may define following Tooltypes:

 ==============================================================
 Tooltype/Parameter                                     Example
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 FONT                                       FONT=helvetica.font
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 FONTSIZE                                           FONTSIZE=15
                           (if you don't use the standard font,
                           you must use both FONT and FONTSIZE)
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 LOGFILE                                 LOGFILE=T:Geometry.log
                                                     (default!)
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 PUBSCREEN                                  PUBSCREEN=Workbench
                                                     (default!)
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 XY                                                     XY=<nn>
                                                  (default = 1)
                 (X/Y-ratio. It is necessary, if horizontal and
                vertical pixel size are different. This depends
                  on the screen mode and monitor you are using.
                    To calculate the correct value for XY, draw
                 a square (Calculate a square and call the menu
                         "DRAW"), measure (on the monitor!) the
                 horizontal face (X) and the vertical face (Y).
                 Divide then X/Y.)
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 CYCLE                                                    CYCLE
                        Buttons in the main window are replaced
                                             by a cycle gadget.
 ==============================================================

 You may also run the program from the shell using the same
 arguments as above, e.g.:

 Geometry FONT=helvetica.font FONTSIZE=15
 LOGFILE=T:Geometry.log PUBSCREEN=Workbench XY=0.87

@endnode

